.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-TMUX" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.39" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-tmux \- Open a tmux pane dashboard for local service logs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose tmux [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Launch or attach to a tracked local run and create one tmux pane per service, each tailing that service's log. tmux is a log dashboard; the existing local supervisor still owns service processes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked local job id to attach to instead of launching a new local run.
.TP
\fB--session\fR \fINAME\fR
tmux session name; defaults to hpc\-compose\-<job\-id>.
.TP
\fB--tmux\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the tmux executable. Default: tmux.
.TP
\fB--no\-attach\fR
Create or update the tmux session without attaching.
.TP
\fB--lines\fR \fILINES\fR
Number of existing log lines each pane should show before following. Default: 100.
.TP
\fB--script\-out\fR \fIOUTPUT\fR
Write the rendered local launcher script to this path when launching.
.TP
\fB--enroot\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the enroot executable. Default: enroot.
.TP
\fB--apptainer\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the apptainer executable. Default: apptainer.
.TP
\fB--singularity\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the singularity executable. Default: singularity.
.TP
\fB--keep\-failed\-prep\fR
Keep failed preparation state on disk for later inspection.
.TP
\fB--skip\-prepare\fR
Skip image preparation and reuse existing artifacts.
.TP
\fB--force\-rebuild\fR
Refresh imported and prepared artifacts before launch.
.TP
\fB--no\-preflight\fR
Skip the preflight phase before launch.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
